# insert(_:at:)

**Instance Method**

Adds a new quantity to the series at the provided date and time.

## Declaration

```swift
func insert(_ quantity: HKQuantity, at date: Date) throws
```

## Parameters

- **quantity**: The quantity to insert.
- **date**: The start date associated with the quantity. If this is the same start date as a previously provided quantity, this quantity replaces the previous one. This method fails with an [doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKError/Code/errorInvalidArgument] error if the `date` parameter is earlier than the series builderâ€™s [doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKQuantitySeriesSampleBuilder/startDate] property.

## Discussion

This method calls [doc://com.apple.healthkit/documentation/HealthKit/HKQuantitySeriesSampleBuilder/insert(_:for:)], passing a date interval with the provided start date, and a duration of `0`.

## Adding Values

- **insert(_:for:)**: Adds a new quantity to the series with the provided date interval.
